      Visual Recording facilitates literacy and understanding.  It's not dumbing-down, it's COMBINING the VISUAL & VERBAL ways of thinking<br/>Einstein's ideas didn't come in word form..they were visual, ephemeral, and he spent years making the words and math fit the images he knew were true.<br/>Graphics help the brain process multiple streams of information and work through complex situations...this is real life, not theory... it can't be reduced to bullet points.  <br/><br/>The graphics are CREATED LIVE, so the group validates what's on them.<br/><br/>lots of different examples & styles: <br/>http://ifvp.org/<br/>http://vizthink.com/<br/>http://www.visual-logic.net/GalleryWVaCRC3.htm<br/>

                  
